We hardly get letters anymore ... have you saved yours? I'm so HAPPY I saved all my mom and dads❤️ ... but old boyfriends too, and letters from my sisters and best friends, and great grandma too . . . they're story of my life, I can dip back into that other century anytime I want! #handwritten #letters #memoriesforlife

This is a very silly letter written by "a boy" to Joe's great great grandmother in 1873. Homemade envelope, about 4" across and 2 ½" down. Beautiful hard-to-read-penmanship, totally flirtatious (difficult to do in a letter!), letters were all they had if they didn't live next door! SO much history in old letters and diaries. #oldletters #dippedpen #history #threecentstamp

I still get wonderful letters 💌. I save them in my "wonderful letter" file ... and if I'm ever feeling sad, I read them, and my heart fills right back up with the juice of the happiness gene and all is well again. #letters #savedletters #blessed

Gentleman Jack, wearing his furry tuxedo and sporting his dandy Hercule Poirot mustache requires lap-sitting first thing in the morning. I MUST sit, with him asleep on my lap, and drink one cup of tea before I can begin my day. Otherwise he's disappointed. Certain things, such as this, and each time I bend to stir his food to make it more palatable for him, are ways I believe will cut my time in purgatory. God is watching us. 😇 Ommmm.

Don't you think that your house asks for what it wants? I had a house once that asked for green and yellow things, and at that time I didn't even like green and yellow all that much. I liked red ~ and pink. But the house said "Paint my floor green" and so I did. It was right. A green floor was perfect! THIS house said, "Get me some quilts (was not picky about color) and an old stove." And so I did . . .💝 In return, this house been berry berry good to me for the last 35 years. 💖 #quilt #listentoyourhouse #home #marthasvineyard #thisoldhouse #1849wasaverygoodyear

To make the eggs easier to peel, steam them (don't boil them) in a steamer for 12-15 min. Use just enough mayo to bind to keep eggy flavor strong, and make two extra so you fill each egg white high with lots of deliciousness. I think a drop or two of Tabasco sauce in the yolk mixture makes them even better. I painted my brothers and me with the Easter Bunny... I distinctly remember seeing there was only mesh over his eyes ~ I could see there was a PERSON in there! Made me feel slightly better. My favorite thing about doing #planks is that it takes literally a minute. Plus, it's rated #1 for an exercise that covers a lot of territory! Strengthens your core, your tummy, and your back. Improves your posture and mental well-being. It's bang for the buck! Start SLOWLY, you can hurt yourself. I'm 76, started by holding plank for 3 seconds... did that a few days, and slowly added more and more until now I do 3 a day for 50 seconds each. ❤️ To you, from me, with love. #exercise #planks #joyfullife #youcandoit

Distilled Genius is a collection of quotations from writers, philosophers, poets, artists, and everyone else, from the beginning of time, through to today. Their brilliance taught me so much; they changed my life. When I ran away from home in my 30s, I desperately searched for the secrets of life in books by my heroes, or people I thought might know. This Thanksgiving everyone is bringing a loved quote to share at the table, funny, inspirational, beautiful, or heart-touching!❤️ Distilled Genius is available in stores, at Amazon, or in my webstore at www.susanbranch.com #quotebook #fivestarsonamazon #illustratedjournal #watercolor #book #pollyanna
